&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot; class=&quot;language-chatlink z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-chatlink&quot; data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source z-chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-begin&quot;&gt;[&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;DQcBHRgdQjsjD24BggEAAIEBAACDAQAA7RIAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADMgAvAFoAAA==&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-end&quot;&gt;]&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;skills&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;21750,10247,10232,10234,29519&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;specializations&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;1,24,66&#x27; data-armory-1-traits=&#x27;701,708,692&#x27; data-armory-24-traits=&#x27;721,1690,733&#x27; data-armory-66-traits=&#x27;2202,2205,2223&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;rotation&quot;&gt;Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To maximise damage on Condition Virtuoso, you should space out your Bladesong Skills in order to upkeep &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2204&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Deadly Blades, as this provides you with a +5% all damage buff. However, by simply comboing a Bladesong Skill with each use of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62560&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladecall (Dagger 2), you will be able to maintain 100% uptime on &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2204&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Deadly Blades.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opener:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62607&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Unstable Bladestorm (Dagger 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62597&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladeturn Requiem&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10174&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Phantasmal Swordsman (Sword 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use Off Cooldown:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62560&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladecall (Dagger 2) + Bladesong Skill&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62607&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Unstable Bladestorm (Dagger 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10174&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Phantasmal Swordsman (Sword 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bladesong Skill Priority:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62597&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladeturn Requiem&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62616&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladesong Sorrow&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62617&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladesong Harmony&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following the above rotation, you will never run out of Bladesong Charges.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;68273&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladesong Distortion is also a very long immune skill, scaling up to a maximum of 3.75 seconds with the number of blade stacks you currently have, and should be your panic button. It can also be used to dodge mechanics on various raids to increase your damage uptime.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;crowd-control&quot;&gt;Crowd Control&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your CC skills are, in order of priority&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CC Skills:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29519&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Humility (BIG CC)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62602&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladesong Dissonance&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10232&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Domination (big DPS loss, not recommended)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10234&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Midnight (very not recommended)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;68273&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bladesong Distortion is also a very long immune skill, up to 3.75 seconds if you use it with maximum stacks of blades, and should be your panic button. It can also be used to dodge mechanics on various raids to increase your damage uptime.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;advanced-tips&quot;&gt;Advanced Tips&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can block attacks with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10280&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Illusionary Riposte (Sword 4), but it is not recommended unless you are very confident of the mechanic. An example of using this to increase DPS would be on Deimos, where it&#x27;s cooldown is short enough to block both the knockback &quot;pizza&quot; mechanic and mindcrush, allowing you to maximise damage uptime on the boss. An example of this can be seen in the demo video below.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;div style=‘clear:both;’&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For fights without CC,&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Replace:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;10247&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Illusions&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29519&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Humility&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;With:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62553&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Rain of Swords&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;24755&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Thousand Cuts&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And use both skills off cooldown for more damage. &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;24755&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Thousand Cuts can be used at any time as it has no cast time and will not interrupt your current action.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;More advanced tips coming soon&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;video&quot;&gt;Video&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
